 ">full entry</a></span></span></span></div><div class="collapse" hclass="collapse" htag="div"><span class="unbox" id="allusion_unbox_1" unbox="wordorigin"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">mid 16th cent. (denoting a pun, metaphor, or parable): from French, or from late Latin <span class="ei">allusio(n-)</span>, from the verb <span class="ei">alludere</span>, from <span class="ei">ad-</span> ‘towards’ + <span class="ei">ludere</span> ‘to play’.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
